\title{"skill builder"}

\taxon{skill}

\meta{description}{"Create new Claude Code Skills with proper YAML frontmatter, progressive disclosure structure, and complete directory organization. Use when you need to build custom skills for specific workflows, generate skill templates, or understand the Claude Skills specification."}

\subtree{
\title{Skill Builder}
\subtree{
\title{What This Skill Does}
\p{Creates production-ready Claude Code Skills with proper YAML frontmatter, progressive disclosure architecture, and complete file/folder structure. This skill guides you through building skills that Claude can autonomously discover and use across all surfaces (Claude.ai, Claude Code, SDK, API).}
}

\subtree{
\title{Prerequisites}
\ul{
\li{Claude Code 2.0+ or Claude.ai with Skills support}
\li{Basic understanding of Markdown and YAML}
\li{Text editor or IDE}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Quick Start}
\subtree{
\title{Creating Your First Skill}
\pre{\startverb
# 1. Create skill directory (MUST be at top level, NOT in subdirectories!)
mkdir -p ~/.claude/skills/my-first-skill

# 2. Create SKILL.md with proper format
cat > ~/.claude/skills/my-first-skill/SKILL.md << 'EOF'
---
name: "My First Skill"
description: "Brief description of what this skill does and when Claude should use it. Maximum 1024 characters."
---

# My First Skill

## What This Skill Does
[Your instructions here]

## Quick Start
[Basic usage]
EOF

# 3. Verify skill is detected
# Restart Claude Code or refresh Claude.ai
\stopverb}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Complete Specification}
\subtree{
\title{📋 YAML Frontmatter (REQUIRED)}
\p{Every SKILL.md \strong{must} start with YAML frontmatter containing exactly two required fields:}

\pre{\startverb
---
name: "Skill Name"                    # REQUIRED: Max 64 chars
description: "What this skill does    # REQUIRED: Max 1024 chars
and when Claude should use it."       # Include BOTH what & when
---
\stopverb}

\subtree{
\title{Field Requirements}
\p{\strong{\code{\startverb name\stopverb}} (REQUIRED):}

\ul{
\li{\strong{Type}: String}
\li{\strong{Max Length}: 64 characters}
\li{\strong{Format}: Human-friendly display name}
\li{\strong{Usage}: Shown in skill lists, UI, and loaded into Claude's system prompt}
\li{\strong{Best Practice}: Use Title Case, be concise and descriptive}
\li{\strong{Examples}:}
\li{✅ "API Documentation Generator"}
\li{✅ "React Component Builder"}
\li{✅ "Database Schema Designer"}
\li{❌ "skill-1" (not descriptive)}
\li{❌ "This is a very long skill name that exceeds sixty-four characters" (too long)}
}

\p{\strong{\code{\startverb description\stopverb}} (REQUIRED):}

\ul{
\li{\strong{Type}: String}
\li{\strong{Max Length}: 1024 characters}
\li{\strong{Format}: Plain text or minimal markdown}
\li{\strong{Content}: MUST include:}
\li{\strong{What} the skill does (functionality)}
\li{\strong{When} Claude should invoke it (trigger conditions)}
\li{\strong{Usage}: Loaded into Claude's system prompt for autonomous matching}
\li{\strong{Best Practice}: Front-load key trigger words, be specific about use cases}
\li{\strong{Examples}:}
\li{✅ "Generate OpenAPI 3.0 documentation from Express.js routes. Use when creating API docs, documenting endpoints, or building API specifications."}
\li{✅ "Create React functional components with TypeScript, hooks, and tests. Use when scaffolding new components or converting class components."}
\li{❌ "A comprehensive guide to API documentation" (no "when" clause)}
\li{❌ "Documentation tool" (too vague)}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{YAML Formatting Rules}
\pre{\startverb
---
# ✅ CORRECT: Simple string
name: "API Builder"
description: "Creates REST APIs with Express and TypeScript."

# ✅ CORRECT: Multi-line description
name: "Full-Stack Generator"
description: "Generates full-stack applications with React frontend and Node.js backend. Use when starting new projects or scaffolding applications."

# ✅ CORRECT: Special characters quoted
name: "JSON:API Builder"
description: "Creates JSON:API compliant endpoints: pagination, filtering, relationships."

# ❌ WRONG: Missing quotes with special chars
name: API:Builder  # YAML parse error!

# ❌ WRONG: Extra fields (ignored but discouraged)
name: "My Skill"
description: "My description"
version: "1.0.0"       # NOT part of spec
author: "Me"           # NOT part of spec
tags: ["dev", "api"]   # NOT part of spec
---
\stopverb}

\p{\strong{Critical}: Only \code{\startverb name\stopverb} and \code{\startverb description\stopverb} are used by Claude. Additional fields are ignored.}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{📂 Directory Structure}
\subtree{
\title{Minimal Skill (Required)}
\pre{\startverb
~/.claude/skills/                    # Personal skills location
└── my-skill/                        # Skill directory (MUST be at top level!)
    └── SKILL.md                     # REQUIRED: Main skill file
\stopverb}

\p{\strong{IMPORTANT}: Skills MUST be directly under \code{\startverb ~/.claude/skills/[skill-name]/\stopverb}. Claude Code does NOT support nested subdirectories or namespaces!}
}

\subtree{
\title{Full-Featured Skill (Recommended)}
\pre{\startverb
~/.claude/skills/
└── my-skill/                        # Top-level skill directory
        ├── SKILL.md                 # REQUIRED: Main skill file
        ├── README.md                # Optional: Human-readable docs
        ├── scripts/                 # Optional: Executable scripts
        │   ├── setup.sh
        │   ├── validate.js
        │   └── deploy.py
        ├── resources/               # Optional: Supporting files
        │   ├── templates/
        │   │   ├── api-template.js
        │   │   └── component.tsx
        │   ├── examples/
        │   │   └── sample-output.json
        │   └── schemas/
        │       └── config-schema.json
        └── docs/                    # Optional: Additional documentation
            ├── ADVANCED.md
            ├── TROUBLESHOOTING.md
            └── API_REFERENCE.md
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Skills Locations}
\p{\strong{Personal Skills} (available across all projects):}

\pre{\startverb
~/.claude/skills/
└── [your-skills]/
\stopverb}

\ul{
\li{\startverb **Path**: `~/.claude/skills/` or `$HOME/.claude/skills/`\stopverb}
\li{\strong{Scope}: Available in all projects for this user}
\li{\strong{Version Control}: NOT committed to git (outside repo)}
\li{\strong{Use Case}: Personal productivity tools, custom workflows}
}

\p{\strong{Project Skills} (team-shared, version controlled):}

\pre{\startverb
<project-root>/.claude/skills/
└── [team-skills]/
\stopverb}

\ul{
\li{\strong{Path}: \code{\startverb .claude/skills/\stopverb} in project root}
\li{\strong{Scope}: Available only in this project}
\li{\strong{Version Control}: SHOULD be committed to git}
\li{\strong{Use Case}: Team workflows, project-specific tools, shared knowledge}
}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{🎯 Progressive Disclosure Architecture}
\p{Claude Code uses a \strong{3-level progressive disclosure system} to scale to 100+ skills without context penalty:}

\subtree{
\title{Level 1: Metadata (Name + Description)}
\p{\strong{Loaded}: At Claude Code startup, always \strong{Size}: ~200 chars per skill \strong{Purpose}: Enable autonomous skill matching \strong{Context}: Loaded into system prompt for ALL skills}

\pre{\startverb
---
name: "API Builder"                   # 11 chars
description: "Creates REST APIs..."   # ~50 chars
---
# Total: ~61 chars per skill
# 100 skills = ~6KB context (minimal!)
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Level 2: SKILL.md Body}
\p{\strong{Loaded}: When skill is triggered/matched \strong{Size}: ~1-10KB typically \strong{Purpose}: Main instructions and procedures \strong{Context}: Only loaded for ACTIVE skills}

\pre{\startverb
# API Builder

## What This Skill Does
[Main instructions - loaded only when skill is active]

## Quick Start
[Basic procedures]

## Step-by-Step Guide
[Detailed instructions]
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Level 3+: Referenced Files}
\p{\strong{Loaded}: On-demand as Claude navigates \strong{Size}: Variable (KB to MB) \strong{Purpose}: Deep reference, examples, schemas \strong{Context}: Loaded only when Claude accesses specific files}

\pre{\startverb
# In SKILL.md
See [Advanced Configuration](docs/ADVANCED.md) for complex scenarios.
See [API Reference](docs/API_REFERENCE.md) for complete documentation.
Use template: `resources/templates/api-template.js`

# Claude will load these files ONLY if needed
\stopverb}

\p{\strong{Benefit}: Install 100+ skills with ~6KB context. Only active skill content (1-10KB) enters context.}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{📝 SKILL.md Content Structure}
\subtree{
\title{Recommended 4-Level Structure}
\pre{\startverb
---
name: "Your Skill Name"
description: "What it does and when to use it"
---

# Your Skill Name

## Level 1: Overview (Always Read First)
Brief 2-3 sentence description of the skill.

## Prerequisites
- Requirement 1
- Requirement 2

## What This Skill Does
1. Primary function
2. Secondary function
3. Key benefit

---

## Level 2: Quick Start (For Fast Onboarding)

### Basic Usage
\stopverb}
}
}
}
}

