}

\subtree{
\title{Inline File Content}
\pre{\startverb
## Example Configuration
See `resources/examples/config.json`:
\stopverb}

\p{{ "option": "value" }}

\pre{\startverb

\stopverb}

\p{\strong{Best Practice}: Keep SKILL.md lean (~2-5KB). Move lengthy content to separate files and reference them. Claude will load only what's needed.}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{✅ Validation Checklist}
\p{Before publishing a skill, verify:}

\p{\strong{YAML Frontmatter}:}

\ul{
\li{[ ] Starts with \code{\startverb ---\stopverb}}
\li{[ ] Contains \code{\startverb name\stopverb} field (max 64 chars)}
\li{[ ] Contains \code{\startverb description\stopverb} field (max 1024 chars)}
\li{[ ] Description includes "what" and "when"}
\li{[ ] Ends with \code{\startverb ---\stopverb}}
\li{[ ] No YAML syntax errors}
}

\p{\strong{File Structure}:}

\ul{
\li{[ ] SKILL.md exists in skill directory}
\li{[ ] Directory is DIRECTLY in \code{\startverb ~/.claude/skills/[skill-name]/\stopverb} or \code{\startverb .claude/skills/[skill-name]/\stopverb}}
\li{[ ] Uses clear, descriptive directory name}
\li{[ ] \strong{NO nested subdirectories} (Claude Code requires top-level structure)}
}

\p{\strong{Content Quality}:}

\ul{
\li{[ ] Level 1 (Overview) is brief and clear}
\li{[ ] Level 2 (Quick Start) shows common use case}
\li{[ ] Level 3 (Details) provides step-by-step guide}
\li{[ ] Level 4 (Reference) links to advanced content}
\li{[ ] Examples are concrete and runnable}
\li{[ ] Troubleshooting section addresses common issues}
}

\p{\strong{Progressive Disclosure}:}

\ul{
\li{[ ] Core instructions in SKILL.md (~2-5KB)}
\li{[ ] Advanced content in separate docs/}
\li{[ ] Large resources in resources/ directory}
\li{[ ] Clear navigation between levels}
}

\p{\strong{Testing}:}

\ul{
\li{[ ] Skill appears in Claude's skill list}
\li{[ ] Description triggers on relevant queries}
\li{[ ] Instructions are clear and actionable}
\li{[ ] Scripts execute successfully (if included)}
\li{[ ] Examples work as documented}
}
}

